WEBVTT

00:01:29.390 --> 00:01:34.950
[Our Dazzling Days]

00:01:35.280 --> 00:01:37.729
[Episode 25]

00:01:45.200 --> 00:01:46.259
What are you doing?

00:01:47.479 --> 00:01:49.200
-What are you working on?
-Oh, you're here.

00:01:49.200 --> 00:01:50.430
Come look at this.

00:01:54.680 --> 00:01:55.680
That wind chime?

00:01:56.840 --> 00:01:58.310
how did you manage to turn it into this?

00:01:58.310 --> 00:02:00.430
It had probably been hanging there
too long,

00:02:00.430 --> 00:02:01.430
exposed to the wind and sun all that time.

00:02:01.430 --> 00:02:02.790
The wood had completely rotted.

00:02:02.790 --> 00:02:05.430
So I thought I'd fix it up.

00:02:06.650 --> 00:02:07.380
Give it a tap.

00:02:10.030 --> 00:02:11.090
Can it make a sound?

00:02:18.400 --> 00:02:19.360
You know,

00:02:19.360 --> 00:02:21.079
this wind chime actually helps

00:02:21.079 --> 00:02:22.360
with your auditory hallucinations.

00:02:22.360 --> 00:02:23.910
Then would it help

00:02:23.910 --> 00:02:24.870
other patients as well?

00:02:24.870 --> 00:02:28.079
Actually, I was just thinking of
discussing it with the Director.

00:02:28.079 --> 00:02:30.800
That electric bell in the hospital is
way too startling.

00:02:30.800 --> 00:02:34.960
I was thinking—why not use this wind chime

00:02:35.280 --> 00:02:37.710
to wake everyone up in the morning,

00:02:37.710 --> 00:02:39.570
call everyone to meals, and so on?

00:02:40.520 --> 00:02:41.760
What are you doing?

00:02:41.790 --> 00:02:43.200
Why aren't you saying anything?

00:02:43.200 --> 00:02:44.120
You should get up now.

00:02:44.120 --> 00:02:46.150
Xiaoman, sit.

00:02:46.400 --> 00:02:47.200
What's wrong?

00:02:47.910 --> 00:02:49.400
I've forgotten

00:02:49.400 --> 00:02:52.200
which comes first—taking my medicine

00:02:52.230 --> 00:02:55.150
or brushing my teeth.

00:02:55.470 --> 00:02:56.270
Are you crazy?

00:02:56.910 --> 00:02:57.520
Brush your teeth first, of course.

00:02:57.520 --> 00:02:58.310
How can you take medicine
without brushing your teeth?

00:02:58.310 --> 00:03:00.910
See? He keeps criticizing me.

00:03:00.910 --> 00:03:02.040
Why listen to him...

00:03:02.400 --> 00:03:03.710
Do whatever you want.

00:03:03.710 --> 00:03:05.240
What do you want to do first?

00:03:05.540 --> 00:03:08.190
I want to use the bathroom first.

00:03:08.480 --> 00:03:09.080
Hold it in!

00:03:09.270 --> 00:03:10.190
You still have to draw.

00:03:10.190 --> 00:03:12.710
You hear that?
He's doing it again.

00:03:12.710 --> 00:03:14.470
It's okay. Go to the toilet if you want.

00:03:14.470 --> 00:03:15.910
He won't dare criticize you.

00:03:15.910 --> 00:03:17.310
He's always controlling me.

00:03:17.310 --> 00:03:18.790
Mind your own business! Get lost! Go back!

00:03:18.790 --> 00:03:19.590
What the hell?

00:03:20.150 --> 00:03:21.550
Who are you criticizing?

00:03:23.280 --> 00:03:25.120
Looks like he's not coming out anymore.

00:03:25.120 --> 00:03:25.920
Did he go back?

00:03:26.120 --> 00:03:28.190
It's okay.
If he comes out again, I'll bite him.

00:03:28.190 --> 00:03:29.000
Go ahead and use the bathroom.

00:03:29.000 --> 00:03:30.400
Thank you, Xiaoman.

00:03:33.150 --> 00:03:34.210
That really hurts.

00:03:42.520 --> 00:03:43.480
My turn now?

00:03:43.510 --> 00:03:44.180
Right.

00:03:45.000 --> 00:03:46.120
Which one is mine?

00:03:46.430 --> 00:03:47.160
Where is Liu?

00:03:47.320 --> 00:03:48.720
Liu went to the bathroom.

00:03:52.590 --> 00:03:53.150
Xiaoman.

00:03:54.400 --> 00:03:56.710
You seem almost fully recovered.

00:03:56.710 --> 00:03:58.710
Shouldn't you be discharged soon?

00:04:00.280 --> 00:04:01.810
What are you talking about?

00:04:01.980 --> 00:04:02.820
What?

00:04:03.630 --> 00:04:05.030
I'm nowhere near better.

00:04:07.870 --> 00:04:08.670
Are you ready?

00:04:08.920 --> 00:04:09.530
Yes.

00:04:13.750 --> 00:04:14.590
Ms. Yan,

00:04:14.590 --> 00:04:17.920
first, congratulations on winning

00:04:18.120 --> 00:04:20.579
the French FMA Design Award
for your design.

00:04:20.630 --> 00:04:21.600
Thank you.

00:04:21.870 --> 00:04:23.920
Could you tell us

00:04:24.680 --> 00:04:27.010
where your design inspiration came from?

00:04:28.720 --> 00:04:31.070
My inspiration came from a moment

00:04:31.430 --> 00:04:33.120
while I was walking down the street.

00:04:33.120 --> 00:04:36.190
I suddenly looked up and saw

00:04:36.310 --> 00:04:37.640
a very beautiful cloud.

00:04:37.680 --> 00:04:40.070
It was windy that day,

00:04:40.070 --> 00:04:42.870
and the clouds kept shifting

00:04:42.920 --> 00:04:44.720
and changing shape in the wind.

00:04:44.900 --> 00:04:47.100
I found that process of transformation

00:04:47.720 --> 00:04:49.510
very romantic and beautiful.

00:04:49.630 --> 00:04:51.430
So I wanted to capture that transformation

00:04:51.430 --> 00:04:54.000
in my own way—

00:04:54.000 --> 00:04:56.000
to preserve that fleeting,

00:04:56.030 --> 00:04:57.150
romantic moment.

00:04:59.040 --> 00:05:03.190
Ms. Yan, you're very brave
and strong-willed.

00:05:04.040 --> 00:05:07.920
However, your award-winning work

00:05:08.030 --> 00:05:10.000
has also attracted some dissenting voices.

00:05:10.000 --> 00:05:12.040
People in the field say your work

00:05:12.040 --> 00:05:14.120
is a "castle in the air" from the East.

00:05:14.720 --> 00:05:16.920
What's your response to that?

00:05:17.310 --> 00:05:21.160
First, I don't think
it's a castle in the air.

00:05:25.430 --> 00:05:27.800
Just like a myth in China—

00:05:27.800 --> 00:05:28.830
Chang'e flying to the moon.

00:05:28.830 --> 00:05:29.750
And yet,

00:05:29.750 --> 00:05:31.680
didn't Armstrong land on the moon?

00:05:32.360 --> 00:05:34.000
So why can't a "castle in the air"

00:05:34.000 --> 00:05:36.750
lead the architecture industry
in a new direction?

00:05:36.750 --> 00:05:40.950
I believe design needs to be

00:05:40.950 --> 00:05:42.010
forward-looking.

00:05:42.920 --> 00:05:43.630
Excuse me.

00:05:45.360 --> 00:05:47.990
Could we give Xiaodan a moment

00:05:48.070 --> 00:05:49.330
to touch up her makeup?

00:05:49.370 --> 00:05:50.370
Please, go ahead.

00:05:53.680 --> 00:05:54.430
Xiaodan,

00:05:54.710 --> 00:05:56.640
you got a bit too worked up just now.

00:05:59.040 --> 00:06:01.050
Do you think their criticism makes sense?

00:06:01.050 --> 00:06:04.100
There is never an absolute right or wrong
in art.

00:06:04.310 --> 00:06:08.720
But when you mentioned
Chang'e flying to the moon,

00:06:09.120 --> 00:06:13.040
it reminded me
that you're a Chinese designer.

00:06:13.210 --> 00:06:15.830
I feel like your designs have had
fewer Eastern elements

00:06:15.830 --> 00:06:20.870
over the past few years.

00:06:31.560 --> 00:06:32.800
Hello, Xia Lei.

00:06:33.120 --> 00:06:33.800
What's up?

00:06:34.390 --> 00:06:35.790
How have you been lately?

00:06:36.720 --> 00:06:38.040
I've been pretty good.

00:06:38.920 --> 00:06:39.520
By the way,

00:06:39.680 --> 00:06:40.390
I have some good news

00:06:40.390 --> 00:06:42.430
I haven't had time to share with you yet.

00:06:42.430 --> 00:06:44.280
My design has won an award.

00:06:45.510 --> 00:06:46.830
I'm in the middle of an interview
right now.

00:06:46.830 --> 00:06:47.630
Really?

00:06:48.000 --> 00:06:49.060
Congratulations.

00:06:49.950 --> 00:06:51.190
You're so amazing.

00:06:51.500 --> 00:06:52.760
So, why did you call me?

00:06:53.190 --> 00:06:55.640
It must be really late
back in China right now, right?

00:06:55.640 --> 00:06:57.040
Yes, it's about... um...

00:07:00.070 --> 00:07:02.830
Xia Lei, what exactly do you want
to tell me?

00:07:02.830 --> 00:07:05.030
I'm still in the middle of an interview.

00:07:07.310 --> 00:07:08.030
Xiaodan,

00:07:08.610 --> 00:07:09.640
your dad is sick.

00:07:11.210 --> 00:07:12.140
What did you say?

00:07:24.560 --> 00:07:25.820
Hurry, put those down.

00:07:25.870 --> 00:07:27.430
These are all big brands.

00:07:27.480 --> 00:07:29.080
I've never used them before.

00:07:29.950 --> 00:07:31.310
Well, they're coming back
from big, glamorous Shanghai,

00:07:31.310 --> 00:07:32.070
so we must have bought some good brands.

00:07:32.070 --> 00:07:33.040
Open the window.

00:07:33.040 --> 00:07:33.770
It smells musty in here.

00:07:33.770 --> 00:07:34.330
Yeah.

00:07:35.190 --> 00:07:35.950
We need to open them all.

00:07:35.950 --> 00:07:37.830
-Let it air out.
-Just put them here.

00:07:37.830 --> 00:07:39.690
The smell in the room isn't great.

00:07:41.800 --> 00:07:44.870
A beautiful day starts with cleaning!

00:07:47.940 --> 00:07:49.800
Open the kitchen windows as well.

00:07:50.830 --> 00:07:51.360
Hurry.

00:07:52.980 --> 00:07:54.040
What's in this box?

00:07:56.390 --> 00:07:57.360
Hang it on the left, at the very top.

00:07:57.360 --> 00:07:58.510
Did it used to hang here?

00:07:58.510 --> 00:08:00.370
You sure you remember correctly?

00:08:00.720 --> 00:08:01.920
Where does this hang?

00:08:02.000 --> 00:08:02.870
This hangs below,

00:08:02.870 --> 00:08:04.870
right under the painting of bamboo.

00:08:05.680 --> 00:08:08.190
Do we really have to put everything back
exactly where it was before?

00:08:08.190 --> 00:08:10.270
Yufen specifically asked me to try to

00:08:10.270 --> 00:08:12.070
put everything back as close to the way

00:08:12.070 --> 00:08:13.920
it was before as possible.

00:08:14.110 --> 00:08:16.910
I've been coming over to clean
these past few days,

00:08:17.060 --> 00:08:19.800
and several people from the plant
ran into me and asked

00:08:19.800 --> 00:08:22.130
why they decided to come back so suddenly.

00:08:22.190 --> 00:08:23.430
But I didn't mention to them

00:08:23.430 --> 00:08:26.040
that Chief Engineer Yan is sick—
not a word.

00:08:26.510 --> 00:08:28.770
You did the right thing not telling them.

00:08:29.920 --> 00:08:31.920
Is... Is this supposed to hang here,

00:08:31.990 --> 00:08:32.590
honey?

00:08:33.809 --> 00:08:34.750
My memory's a little hazy.

00:08:34.750 --> 00:08:37.169
T-That's right. Then the bamboo painting
shouldn't be hung there.

00:08:37.169 --> 00:08:37.720
Right?

00:08:50.640 --> 00:08:51.290
Xiaoman.

00:08:52.200 --> 00:08:53.080
Xiaoman, the Chime Ringer.

00:08:53.080 --> 00:08:54.210
Waking everyone up?

00:08:55.840 --> 00:08:57.840
You've got great energy, young man.

00:08:58.160 --> 00:08:59.910
Looks like you've recovered pretty well.

00:08:59.910 --> 00:09:00.810
I've been doing pretty well lately.

00:09:00.810 --> 00:09:03.070
I've been
sleeping through the night lately.

00:09:03.070 --> 00:09:05.430
And I think the medicine here

00:09:05.510 --> 00:09:06.670
is really working.

00:09:07.630 --> 00:09:08.750
Medication

00:09:08.750 --> 00:09:09.910
is only part of it.

00:09:10.150 --> 00:09:12.080
The psychotherapy we talked about
last time

00:09:12.080 --> 00:09:13.360
is also very important.

00:09:13.360 --> 00:09:14.030
The sound of the wind chime

00:09:14.030 --> 00:09:15.890
has had a positive influence on you.

00:09:15.890 --> 00:09:17.630
Well, when you're in a good mood,

00:09:17.630 --> 00:09:19.440
you naturally recover more quickly.

00:09:19.440 --> 00:09:20.150
Right.

00:09:20.150 --> 00:09:21.440
And one more thing, Xiaoman,

00:09:21.440 --> 00:09:23.630
our hospital beds have been

00:09:23.960 --> 00:09:25.020
a bit tight lately.

00:09:27.120 --> 00:09:28.670
But I... I haven't fully recovered yet.

00:09:28.670 --> 00:09:30.270
I-I-I'm not completely well yet.

00:09:30.270 --> 00:09:31.120
A-And didn't you

00:09:31.120 --> 00:09:32.720
promise Officer Leng

00:09:32.790 --> 00:09:34.810
that I wouldn't be discharged
until I was fully cured?

00:09:34.810 --> 00:09:36.020
Otherwise, I'd be a danger out there.

00:09:36.020 --> 00:09:37.310
I'm not saying you'll be discharged.

00:09:37.310 --> 00:09:39.310
Okay then. I've thought about it

00:09:39.600 --> 00:09:40.650
carefully.

00:09:40.680 --> 00:09:42.060
I don't want to just stay here

00:09:42.060 --> 00:09:42.700
for free.

00:09:42.840 --> 00:09:44.240
I'm thinking that I could work here

00:09:44.240 --> 00:09:46.220
to pay for my stay. What do you think?

00:09:46.220 --> 00:09:48.050
I-If it really comes down to it,
how about...

00:09:48.050 --> 00:09:49.550
how about you hire me
as a nursing assistant?

00:09:49.550 --> 00:09:50.600
Okay then.

00:09:50.840 --> 00:09:51.440
In a couple of days,

00:09:51.440 --> 00:09:52.630
I'll give you a test.

00:09:52.900 --> 00:09:54.570
If it shows you've recovered,

00:09:54.740 --> 00:09:55.570
we can consider it.

00:09:55.570 --> 00:09:57.140
Sure. I can handle it.

00:09:58.690 --> 00:09:59.510
In a few days,

00:09:59.510 --> 00:10:01.080
we'll have a new patient.

00:10:01.100 --> 00:10:02.940
He doesn't have any manic symptoms.

00:10:02.940 --> 00:10:04.660
I'm planning to have him room with you.

00:10:04.660 --> 00:10:05.330
Is that okay?

00:10:05.330 --> 00:10:07.300
Sure, I'll help you chat with him.

00:10:07.440 --> 00:10:08.940
I'll have a good chat with him,
help him sort his head out,

00:10:08.940 --> 00:10:10.120
and get him on his way home.

00:10:10.120 --> 00:10:11.630
One, two, one.

00:10:12.210 --> 00:10:15.730
Go, go, let's go together.

00:10:16.440 --> 00:10:18.030
Go, go.

00:10:21.750 --> 00:10:25.010
Xiaoman, you're really getting
better and better at this!

00:10:25.430 --> 00:10:26.490
Xiu, open the door.

00:10:26.550 --> 00:10:27.060
Come on.

00:10:27.600 --> 00:10:29.000
Let's go back to the room.

00:10:33.000 --> 00:10:34.000
Moved in already?

00:10:35.000 --> 00:10:36.670
You must be my new roommate.

00:10:38.480 --> 00:10:39.790
I'm in the next bed.

00:10:40.080 --> 00:10:40.870
I'm Xiaoman.

00:10:47.710 --> 00:10:49.570
You're indeed not the manic type—

00:10:49.790 --> 00:10:50.920
more the aloof type.

00:10:51.240 --> 00:10:51.970
It's okay.

00:10:51.990 --> 00:10:54.440
Hope we get along well.

00:11:08.030 --> 00:11:09.960
You're Mr. Gu, right? Our teacher?

00:11:10.830 --> 00:11:11.670
Who are you?

00:11:12.020 --> 00:11:12.950
It really is you!

00:11:13.960 --> 00:11:14.750
Mr. Gu!

00:11:15.550 --> 00:11:16.880
It's me, Zhang Xiaoman!

00:11:17.170 --> 00:11:18.630
Back then, you were actually the one

00:11:18.630 --> 00:11:20.430
supervising our exam that year.

00:11:20.600 --> 00:11:21.860
Do you still remember?

00:11:22.320 --> 00:11:23.920
You do look kind of familiar.

00:11:24.720 --> 00:11:26.550
And I had two classmates

00:11:27.100 --> 00:11:28.700
who cheated during the exam.

00:11:28.910 --> 00:11:29.600
You caught them.

00:11:29.600 --> 00:11:30.670
Do you still remember that?

00:11:30.670 --> 00:11:31.650
My two classmates—

00:11:31.650 --> 00:11:32.960
a boy and a girl.

00:11:33.080 --> 00:11:34.360
We were taking the exam,

00:11:34.360 --> 00:11:35.510
doing the multiple-choice questions.

00:11:35.510 --> 00:11:36.720
The boy used a ruler

00:11:36.900 --> 00:11:40.140
and marked the answers on it.

00:11:40.270 --> 00:11:41.320
When they swapped rulers,

00:11:41.320 --> 00:11:42.510
you spotted it immediately.

00:11:42.510 --> 00:11:43.750
You caught them right then.

00:11:43.750 --> 00:11:45.030
They had it really bad afterward—

00:11:45.030 --> 00:11:47.090
going home crying and making a scene.

00:11:50.150 --> 00:11:52.350
You're a fortune-teller or something?

00:11:52.420 --> 00:11:57.060
It was... Xia Lei and Yan Xiaodan.

00:11:57.400 --> 00:11:58.210
Right!

00:11:58.640 --> 00:11:59.640
It was them!

00:12:00.080 --> 00:12:01.790
You still remember, don't you?

00:12:01.790 --> 00:12:03.120
They're doing really well now!

00:12:03.120 --> 00:12:04.370
One's in Shanghai, the other in France.

00:12:04.370 --> 00:12:05.790
Quite impressive, aren't they?

00:12:05.790 --> 00:12:06.480
No wonder I could

00:12:06.480 --> 00:12:08.110
catch them cheating back then—

00:12:08.110 --> 00:12:09.840
their method was so subtle.

00:12:10.540 --> 00:12:12.490
Turns out it was the "you" of today

00:12:12.510 --> 00:12:14.400
who told me about it.

00:12:14.440 --> 00:12:17.030
Then I could tell my past self,

00:12:17.030 --> 00:12:18.550
allowing my past self

00:12:19.100 --> 00:12:20.310
to catch them.

00:12:23.430 --> 00:12:25.830
That's how parallel worlds are connected.

00:12:39.620 --> 00:12:40.920
This cigarette's good, huh?

00:12:40.920 --> 00:12:41.980
Yeah, pretty good.

00:12:43.970 --> 00:12:44.660
Who's that?

00:12:47.600 --> 00:12:49.800
Isn't that Mr. Yan, Chief Engineer Yan?

00:12:51.540 --> 00:12:52.840
Well, you're back.

00:12:53.100 --> 00:12:54.430
Went grocery shopping.

00:12:54.910 --> 00:12:55.750
You went grocery shopping?

00:12:55.750 --> 00:12:56.510
Yes, yes.

00:12:57.270 --> 00:12:58.630
Drop by sometime!

00:12:58.630 --> 00:12:59.120
Okay.

00:13:07.910 --> 00:13:09.080
We're home!

00:13:09.910 --> 00:13:10.680
We're home.

00:13:12.870 --> 00:13:13.930
This place is good.

00:13:15.390 --> 00:13:19.200
T-The East Chemical Plant
feels more like home.

00:13:19.200 --> 00:13:21.260
Yeah, the plant feels more like home.

00:13:21.720 --> 00:13:22.780
This place is nice.

00:13:26.670 --> 00:13:27.630
Hurry up.

00:13:28.270 --> 00:13:30.270
Slow down, Yan.

00:13:30.840 --> 00:13:32.510
Slow down.

00:13:33.670 --> 00:13:36.150
Careful, or you'll fall, Yan.

00:13:37.790 --> 00:13:39.080
What's the rush, Yan?

00:13:39.080 --> 00:13:40.720
You don't even know the way.

00:13:43.670 --> 00:13:46.190
I know. How could I forget?

00:13:46.480 --> 00:13:48.390
202, Unit 2, Building 4.

00:13:49.540 --> 00:13:51.000
How could I forget my home?

00:13:51.240 --> 00:13:52.150
Hurry up!

00:13:52.150 --> 00:13:54.120
I can barely keep up with you.

00:13:54.140 --> 00:13:55.110
See?

00:13:55.440 --> 00:13:56.370
We're home.

00:13:56.600 --> 00:13:58.000
Yes, we're home.

00:13:58.000 --> 00:13:59.080
Everything is fine now, okay?

00:13:59.080 --> 00:14:00.240
Unit 4.

00:14:01.710 --> 00:14:03.370
-You're all fine now.
-Hurry.

00:14:24.030 --> 00:14:26.510
We really have to thank Xia Lei's parents.

00:14:28.400 --> 00:14:30.530
They cleaned the apartment so nicely.

00:14:44.600 --> 00:14:47.000
Yan. Come take your medicine.

00:14:47.120 --> 00:14:47.840
Okay.

00:14:48.270 --> 00:14:50.000
This is your favorite spot.

00:14:50.120 --> 00:14:50.750
Right?

00:14:51.240 --> 00:14:52.570
Put it here. Put it here.

00:14:52.980 --> 00:14:53.950
Give me your coat.

00:14:53.950 --> 00:14:55.580
I've got it. It's fine.

00:14:56.340 --> 00:14:57.940
I'll count the pills for you.

00:14:59.630 --> 00:15:01.660
This one—one pill.

00:15:01.700 --> 00:15:02.630
One. Okay.

00:15:03.080 --> 00:15:03.960
This one—two pills.

00:15:03.960 --> 00:15:04.840
Two of these.

00:15:04.960 --> 00:15:05.630
Okay?

00:15:05.630 --> 00:15:06.150
Okay.

00:15:07.320 --> 00:15:07.960
Someone is here.

00:15:07.960 --> 00:15:09.490
Well, you're already back!

00:15:09.670 --> 00:15:10.440
You're here!

00:15:10.440 --> 00:15:10.910
Yufen!

00:15:10.910 --> 00:15:12.120
I'll be right there!

00:15:13.510 --> 00:15:13.960
Okay.

00:15:15.840 --> 00:15:17.000
You're here!

00:15:17.000 --> 00:15:18.440
I knew you'd be here at this time!

00:15:18.440 --> 00:15:20.270
I figured you wouldn't have
had a chance to go shopping.

00:15:20.270 --> 00:15:21.960
I didn't dare buy vegetables too early.

00:15:21.960 --> 00:15:22.790
Put them in the fridge.

00:15:22.790 --> 00:15:25.080
Our home is already packed with

00:15:25.080 --> 00:15:26.150
everything you brought.

00:15:26.150 --> 00:15:27.750
And you went and bought more.

00:15:28.870 --> 00:15:29.320
Have a seat.

00:15:29.320 --> 00:15:30.050
You're here.

00:15:30.480 --> 00:15:31.870
Old Yan, you remember who this is, right?

00:15:31.870 --> 00:15:32.840
Lei's mom.

00:15:34.520 --> 00:15:35.510
How is Lei?

00:15:37.390 --> 00:15:38.240
He's doing great.

00:15:38.240 --> 00:15:39.160
Promising kid.

00:15:39.620 --> 00:15:40.240
Good.

00:15:41.150 --> 00:15:42.210
Good, good for Lei.

00:15:44.670 --> 00:15:45.360
This time,

00:15:45.360 --> 00:15:47.820
thank you
for cleaning everything up for me.

00:15:48.080 --> 00:15:50.450
Otherwise, I was afraid
he wouldn't recognize...

00:15:50.450 --> 00:15:52.710
Yan, why are you taking your pills again?

00:15:53.610 --> 00:15:56.140
You already took them!
Don't take them again!

00:15:56.340 --> 00:15:57.140
I didn't.

00:15:57.510 --> 00:15:59.110
You just took them.

00:15:59.200 --> 00:16:00.150
When Xia Lei's mom came,

00:16:00.150 --> 00:16:01.750
you just swallowed the pills.

00:16:01.750 --> 00:16:03.600
You can't take more.

00:16:04.120 --> 00:16:06.270
How did you take this one too?

00:16:06.270 --> 00:16:07.600
What's going on now?

00:16:07.600 --> 00:16:09.550
He just took his medicine
and took it again.

00:16:09.550 --> 00:16:10.360
Another dose.

00:16:10.390 --> 00:16:12.860
T-This kind—take one. One.

00:16:13.480 --> 00:16:15.140
And take two of the other kind.

00:16:16.090 --> 00:16:17.040
Half a pill?

00:16:17.060 --> 00:16:18.590
Alright, stop taking them.

00:16:18.680 --> 00:16:19.940
Put the medicine away.

00:16:20.510 --> 00:16:21.750
One and a half pills.

00:16:21.870 --> 00:16:22.960
Why are you being so fierce?

00:16:22.960 --> 00:16:24.720
You made our nurse cry.

00:16:24.720 --> 00:16:25.360
Just take it.

00:16:25.360 --> 00:16:26.720
Let her cry all she wants!
What's that got to do with me?

00:16:26.720 --> 00:16:28.000
I'm just not going to take it!

00:16:28.000 --> 00:16:30.400
Oh my, calm down.

00:16:30.630 --> 00:16:31.720
I'm the head nurse.

00:16:31.720 --> 00:16:33.270
I don't care what "head" you are!

00:16:33.270 --> 00:16:34.240
Be whatever you want!

00:16:34.240 --> 00:16:35.270
I'm not taking it!

00:16:35.360 --> 00:16:36.270
I'm telling you,

00:16:36.270 --> 00:16:38.400
if you didn't look like my second aunt,

00:16:38.600 --> 00:16:40.360
I would've fired you already,
you know that?

00:16:40.360 --> 00:16:41.570
Then listen to me, nephew—

00:16:41.570 --> 00:16:42.600
come on, take your medicine.

00:16:42.600 --> 00:16:44.130
Don't pretend we're close!

00:16:44.470 --> 00:16:46.720
I spent 50 million yuan
building this hospital!

00:16:46.720 --> 00:16:47.770
Not just you,

00:16:47.810 --> 00:16:49.790
I'll even fire the Director! Believe it?

00:16:49.790 --> 00:16:51.790
Take your medicine before you fire me.

00:16:51.790 --> 00:16:52.790
I'm not taking it!

00:16:52.960 --> 00:16:53.320
You...

00:16:53.320 --> 00:16:54.120
What's wrong?

00:16:54.370 --> 00:16:55.630
Xiaoman, thank goodness you're here.

00:16:55.630 --> 00:16:56.750
Talk to him, will you?

00:16:56.750 --> 00:16:58.010
He won't take his meds.

00:16:59.080 --> 00:17:00.270
Sir, you're new here?

00:17:00.270 --> 00:17:01.120
Who are you?

00:17:02.020 --> 00:17:03.590
I'm also a patient here.

00:17:03.610 --> 00:17:05.069
I stay in the room up front.

00:17:06.589 --> 00:17:07.319
A patient?

00:17:07.349 --> 00:17:09.210
Then how come you get to wear a hat?

00:17:09.680 --> 00:17:11.030
I earned points for taking my medicine.

00:17:11.030 --> 00:17:12.920
Earn enough points
and you get to wear a hat.

00:17:12.920 --> 00:17:13.849
Come in. Come on.

00:17:15.400 --> 00:17:17.060
What's wrong? Why are you mad?

00:17:17.240 --> 00:17:18.300
Look at this place.

00:17:19.349 --> 00:17:22.589
Even my housekeeper's bathroom
is bigger than this room!

00:17:22.680 --> 00:17:23.750
Get me a suite immediately!

00:17:23.750 --> 00:17:25.010
Then I want a suite too!

00:17:26.480 --> 00:17:28.200
All the rooms here are like this.

00:17:28.200 --> 00:17:29.550
You're here for treatment,

00:17:29.550 --> 00:17:31.070
not for a vacation.

00:17:31.850 --> 00:17:32.980
They don't have any.

00:17:33.880 --> 00:17:34.920
If there's no suite, I'm not staying.

00:17:34.920 --> 00:17:36.350
And I'm not taking my meds!

00:17:36.350 --> 00:17:37.460
Look at you.

00:17:37.550 --> 00:17:39.440
What were you thinking
when you built this hospital?

00:17:39.440 --> 00:17:40.680
The rooms are so small,

00:17:40.680 --> 00:17:41.680
hot, and damp!

00:17:41.680 --> 00:17:42.350
What the hell is this?

00:17:42.350 --> 00:17:43.160
What?

00:17:43.640 --> 00:17:44.240
Listen up,

00:17:44.240 --> 00:17:46.030
I spent 50 million yuan
building this hospital.

00:17:46.030 --> 00:17:47.550
I didn't know I'd be staying here!

00:17:47.550 --> 00:17:48.510
If I had known,

00:17:48.510 --> 00:17:49.590
I would've spent another 50 million

00:17:49.590 --> 00:17:50.990
to decorate it properly!

00:17:51.070 --> 00:17:53.200
Man, you built this hospital?

00:17:53.200 --> 00:17:54.000
What?

00:17:55.070 --> 00:17:57.270
Then I have to say,
what were you thinking?

00:17:57.270 --> 00:17:59.000
You built a hospital
without a sports field?

00:17:59.000 --> 00:18:00.350
The place where we do aerobics every day

00:18:00.350 --> 00:18:00.920
doesn't even get any sun.

00:18:00.920 --> 00:18:01.550
It's right by the stairs.

00:18:01.550 --> 00:18:03.110
I'm always afraid I'll tumble down.

00:18:03.110 --> 00:18:04.310
You don't even have a place to exercise?

00:18:04.310 --> 00:18:05.110
Exactly!

00:18:05.740 --> 00:18:06.670
Come here. Come.

00:18:08.920 --> 00:18:10.000
I have an idea.

00:18:10.220 --> 00:18:11.500
See that hill peak?

00:18:11.920 --> 00:18:13.680
I'll spend another 60 million

00:18:13.790 --> 00:18:15.550
to blow that hilltop up.

00:18:15.630 --> 00:18:16.760
After blowing it up,

00:18:16.910 --> 00:18:20.020
I'll build a sky gym on top.

00:18:20.160 --> 00:18:22.110
That way, I can work out

00:18:22.310 --> 00:18:24.110
while overlooking my properties,

00:18:24.110 --> 00:18:25.530
including this hospital.

00:18:25.530 --> 00:18:26.530
Right there.

00:18:26.560 --> 00:18:28.350
That spot right there has the best view!

00:18:28.350 --> 00:18:29.550
That's the best spot.

00:18:29.550 --> 00:18:30.400
What do you think?

00:18:30.400 --> 00:18:31.750
I think...

00:18:33.120 --> 00:18:34.070
it's doable.

00:18:34.510 --> 00:18:35.750
Man, it's like this.

00:18:36.510 --> 00:18:38.880
I've studied this hill for a long time.

00:18:39.430 --> 00:18:41.900
I think flattening it isn't
really worth it, don't you think?

00:18:41.900 --> 00:18:44.240
It's better to hollow it out
and make a sky pool.

00:18:44.240 --> 00:18:46.160
Behind it, build an artificial sea.

00:18:46.160 --> 00:18:47.440
Gardens on the left.

00:18:47.480 --> 00:18:48.270
So when you wake up,

00:18:48.270 --> 00:18:49.310
you can see whatever you want to see.

00:18:49.310 --> 00:18:50.270
You have the sea,

00:18:50.350 --> 00:18:51.880
the mountains, and the lake.

00:18:51.880 --> 00:18:53.610
Right? You've got everything.

00:18:53.920 --> 00:18:55.590
Once the whole thing is built out,

00:18:55.590 --> 00:18:57.310
every room here must have

00:18:57.400 --> 00:19:00.070
a 24-hour temperature-controlled
infinity pool.

00:19:00.070 --> 00:19:02.440
Right inside, right by the bed, right?

00:19:02.640 --> 00:19:04.510
And each pool should have a spout.

00:19:04.720 --> 00:19:05.850
And what comes out of it?

00:19:05.850 --> 00:19:09.310
Hot spring water from
the underwater volcano in the Bohai Sea.

00:19:09.400 --> 00:19:11.240
Imagine soaking in a hot spring here
every day. How nice would that be?

00:19:11.240 --> 00:19:11.720
That would be amazing.

00:19:11.720 --> 00:19:12.960
Well, at that time,
we could sit by the pool

00:19:12.960 --> 00:19:15.310
with fruit on the table

00:19:15.310 --> 00:19:17.480
and some beer!

00:19:17.480 --> 00:19:19.510
A bite of fruit, a sip of beer—
down the hatch.

00:19:19.510 --> 00:19:20.310
Stop.

00:19:22.310 --> 00:19:24.680
Young man, I'm sick,

00:19:25.080 --> 00:19:26.400
but I'm not stupid.

00:19:28.000 --> 00:19:31.510
How can you wash down fruit with beer?

00:19:31.820 --> 00:19:34.180
You have to use plain water, right?

00:19:34.300 --> 00:19:36.160
What is this? Plain water, right?

00:19:36.480 --> 00:19:36.960
See?

00:19:39.860 --> 00:19:42.320
It's safe and healthy this way.
Understand?

00:19:42.590 --> 00:19:43.310
Yes.

00:19:45.550 --> 00:19:46.200
Wait, no.

00:19:47.510 --> 00:19:48.750
What did I just eat?

00:19:49.920 --> 00:19:50.510
Fruit.

00:19:51.160 --> 00:19:52.830
Oh, fruit. That's fine.

00:19:52.870 --> 00:19:53.920
The alcohol hasn't arrived yet.

00:19:53.920 --> 00:19:55.510
I'll get some for you in a couple of days.

00:19:55.510 --> 00:19:57.110
Can you get me some baijiu?

00:19:57.270 --> 00:19:58.240
That stuff is so strong

00:19:58.240 --> 00:19:59.400
it'll give you a headache
after drinking it.

00:19:59.400 --> 00:20:00.200
Xiaoman.

00:20:01.160 --> 00:20:01.750
Stop chatting.

00:20:01.750 --> 00:20:03.010
Time to ring the chime.

00:20:03.200 --> 00:20:04.440
Okay, okay. I need to go
ring the chime, man.

00:20:04.440 --> 00:20:05.110
Young man!

00:20:05.590 --> 00:20:07.790
From now on, come hang out in my room
when you're free.

00:20:07.790 --> 00:20:08.720
Chat with me.

00:20:08.920 --> 00:20:11.270
Sure. But in the mornings,
I have to wake others up.

00:20:11.270 --> 00:20:12.920
I have my own business and work to do.

00:20:12.920 --> 00:20:13.510
I'm quite busy.

00:20:13.510 --> 00:20:13.830
Okay.

00:20:13.830 --> 00:20:14.640
Call me if you need anything.

00:20:14.640 --> 00:20:15.590
I'm just a few rooms down.

00:20:15.590 --> 00:20:16.250
Okay, good.

00:20:16.310 --> 00:20:16.920
What's your name?

00:20:16.920 --> 00:20:17.790
My name is "Chime Ringer."

00:20:17.790 --> 00:20:19.050
No, my name is Xiaoman.

00:20:19.790 --> 00:20:20.750
Xiaoman, the Chime Ringer.

00:20:20.750 --> 00:20:22.350
Yeah, I need to ring the chime.

00:20:22.350 --> 00:20:23.400
Call me if you need anything, man!

00:20:23.400 --> 00:20:24.460
Alright, Charmer!

00:20:27.070 --> 00:20:27.750
Xiaoman.

00:20:28.310 --> 00:20:29.400
It's been quite a while now,

00:20:29.400 --> 00:20:31.000
and you haven't developed
any new symptoms.

00:20:31.000 --> 00:20:32.750
I think your current condition

00:20:32.750 --> 00:20:35.010
fully meets the criteria for discharge.

00:20:35.550 --> 00:20:38.400
Director Huang, I think I still
need more treatment.

00:20:38.400 --> 00:20:40.260
You can't hide away here forever.

00:20:41.200 --> 00:20:42.160
Do you know why I had you

00:20:42.160 --> 00:20:44.550
and Chunchun go out
to do procurement the other day?

00:20:44.550 --> 00:20:45.810
It's because I believe

00:20:45.960 --> 00:20:47.160
you're now fully capable of

00:20:47.160 --> 00:20:48.880
adapting to life outside these walls.

00:20:48.880 --> 00:20:50.550
What you need isn't medication—

00:20:50.550 --> 00:20:53.480
you need to overcome
what's holding you back inside.

00:20:53.550 --> 00:20:54.680
Call the patient in.

00:20:54.680 --> 00:20:56.480
Next, No. 27.

00:20:56.640 --> 00:20:57.270
That's us.

00:20:57.270 --> 00:20:58.510
Understood, Director Huang.

00:20:58.510 --> 00:20:59.830
I'll... I'll head back to the room now.

00:20:59.830 --> 00:21:01.430
Alright. Get some good rest.

00:21:01.510 --> 00:21:02.480
No. 27, right?

00:21:02.480 --> 00:21:03.750
Yes, No. 27.

00:21:05.400 --> 00:21:06.530
Chief Engineer Yan?

00:21:07.030 --> 00:21:08.680
This young man looks really familiar.

00:21:08.680 --> 00:21:10.010
Are you here to visit me?

00:21:10.590 --> 00:21:11.320
Yan Wenyuan.

00:21:12.240 --> 00:21:12.920
You're Yan Wenyuan, right?

00:21:12.920 --> 00:21:15.280
Come in. Patient and family,
please come in.

00:21:15.280 --> 00:21:16.720
A young man from the plant.

00:21:16.720 --> 00:21:17.250
Xiaoman.

00:21:18.440 --> 00:21:19.030
Have a seat.

00:21:19.030 --> 00:21:20.240
-Okay.
-Okay.

00:21:47.830 --> 00:21:48.550
Auntie.

00:21:48.580 --> 00:21:49.180
Xiaoman.

00:21:50.170 --> 00:21:51.720
What's wrong with Chief Engineer Yan?

00:21:51.720 --> 00:21:52.790
Alzheimer's.

00:21:53.200 --> 00:21:54.110
That's just how it is.

00:21:54.110 --> 00:21:56.240
It's been going on for quite a while now.

00:21:56.240 --> 00:21:57.070
Everyone calls it

00:21:57.070 --> 00:21:58.310
senile confusion.

00:21:58.910 --> 00:22:00.110
He just keeps thinking

00:22:00.110 --> 00:22:02.680
he's still working at the plant
and that his colleagues

00:22:02.680 --> 00:22:05.960
who passed away long ago are still alive.

00:22:06.270 --> 00:22:07.880
So the doctors in Shanghai

00:22:07.880 --> 00:22:09.750
suggested I bring him back
to a familiar environment.

00:22:09.750 --> 00:22:11.510
It might help his condition.

00:22:11.530 --> 00:22:14.650
Yes, that's called
positive environmental influence.

00:22:14.650 --> 00:22:16.560
I-It will help him.

00:22:17.130 --> 00:22:18.760
So, I brought him back.

00:22:24.400 --> 00:22:25.030
Auntie.

00:22:26.350 --> 00:22:29.920
Um, I'm sort of
a nursing assistant here now.

00:22:30.310 --> 00:22:31.960
If Chief Engineer Yan needs anything,

00:22:31.960 --> 00:22:32.790
just tell me.

00:22:32.790 --> 00:22:33.720
I can help.

00:22:33.790 --> 00:22:35.030
Okay, sure.

00:22:35.200 --> 00:22:36.200
Thank you, Xiaoman.

00:22:36.200 --> 00:22:36.860
No problem.

00:22:40.350 --> 00:22:40.920
Xiaoman.

00:22:42.070 --> 00:22:43.960
I have a favor to ask you.

00:22:44.920 --> 00:22:47.030
Please don't tell others

00:22:47.750 --> 00:22:49.110
about his illness.

00:22:49.840 --> 00:22:51.030
Okay, I understand.

00:22:52.590 --> 00:22:53.200
What's all this?

00:22:53.200 --> 00:22:55.000
What are you doing?

00:22:55.440 --> 00:22:56.350
What are you doing?

00:22:56.350 --> 00:22:57.110
I just tidied it all up.

00:22:57.110 --> 00:22:58.640
W-Where is my work uniform?

00:22:58.750 --> 00:23:00.030
What do you need your uniform for?

00:23:00.030 --> 00:23:01.440
I'm going to the plant to work.

00:23:01.440 --> 00:23:03.110
What are you going to the plant for?

00:23:03.110 --> 00:23:05.000
Safe production is very important.

00:23:05.000 --> 00:23:05.510
I'm telling you,

00:23:05.510 --> 00:23:07.000
if I don't keep an eye on them
for even a day,

00:23:07.000 --> 00:23:08.350
something will go wrong.

00:23:08.350 --> 00:23:10.200
You've already retired.

00:23:10.200 --> 00:23:12.330
Well, where could my uniform have gone?

00:23:12.330 --> 00:23:14.200
There are uniforms at the plant.

00:23:14.200 --> 00:23:15.850
This isn't my uniform!

00:23:15.880 --> 00:23:17.030
Just wear this, okay?

00:23:17.030 --> 00:23:17.960
They have uniforms at the plant.

00:23:17.960 --> 00:23:18.960
Hurry up and put it on.

00:23:18.960 --> 00:23:20.350
It's cold outside.

00:23:20.790 --> 00:23:21.550
Okay, okay.

00:23:21.550 --> 00:23:22.480
I'm heading out.

00:23:22.590 --> 00:23:23.590
I'll go with you.

00:23:23.830 --> 00:23:24.350
Okay.

00:23:27.880 --> 00:23:29.010
So dilly-dallying.

00:23:29.920 --> 00:23:30.590
Mom!

00:23:30.590 --> 00:23:31.640
Sweetie!

00:23:31.960 --> 00:23:33.370
Our daughter is back!

00:23:34.590 --> 00:23:35.240
Dad.

00:23:35.240 --> 00:23:36.070
Did you miss me?

00:23:36.070 --> 00:23:37.310
Of course I did.

00:23:37.510 --> 00:23:38.880
Look at you.

00:23:38.960 --> 00:23:40.480
You didn't even tell us
you were coming back.

00:23:40.480 --> 00:23:41.270
Give me your suitcase.

00:23:41.270 --> 00:23:43.070
Come on, I'll put it in your room.

00:23:44.070 --> 00:23:45.920
Sweetie, our daughter is back.

00:23:46.670 --> 00:23:49.320
Mom, how could you
keep Dad's illness from me?

00:23:49.590 --> 00:23:51.070
It's fine. Nothing serious.

00:23:51.070 --> 00:23:51.870
It's nothing.

00:23:52.160 --> 00:23:53.350
Why are you two chatting over there?

00:23:53.350 --> 00:23:54.270
Come on, let's go inside.

00:23:54.270 --> 00:23:54.880
Okay.

00:23:55.120 --> 00:23:56.250
Hurry, come inside.

00:23:57.160 --> 00:23:58.590
Dad, I want an apple.

00:23:58.590 --> 00:23:59.640
Wash one for me.

00:23:59.640 --> 00:24:00.880
Go wash an apple.

00:24:01.110 --> 00:24:03.110
You wash them the best. You go.

00:24:04.350 --> 00:24:05.480
Sweetie, come here.

00:24:07.910 --> 00:24:09.110
How's his condition?

00:24:09.700 --> 00:24:11.690
It's not a big problem.

00:24:11.720 --> 00:24:12.960
The doctor said

00:24:12.980 --> 00:24:15.910
that as long as he stays
in a familiar environment,

00:24:16.590 --> 00:24:17.830
he'll recover quickly.

00:24:17.830 --> 00:24:18.560
Don't worry.

00:24:18.820 --> 00:24:21.070
He just gets a little forgetful sometimes.

00:24:21.070 --> 00:24:23.000
He always thinks he's still at work.

00:24:23.000 --> 00:24:25.200
But usually, he doesn't need much care.

00:24:25.400 --> 00:24:26.550
Don't worry too much,

00:24:26.550 --> 00:24:27.100
okay?

00:24:28.370 --> 00:24:30.130
Do the people at the plant know?

00:24:30.660 --> 00:24:31.590
For things like this,

00:24:31.590 --> 00:24:33.190
it's better to keep it quiet.

00:24:35.230 --> 00:24:35.880
Mom,

00:24:36.110 --> 00:24:37.640
it's been hard on you alone.

00:24:38.310 --> 00:24:39.400
I'm fine.

00:24:39.400 --> 00:24:40.640
Really, I'm fine.

00:24:40.960 --> 00:24:42.920
Look, you came all this way.

00:24:42.920 --> 00:24:44.120
You must have jet lag.

00:24:44.270 --> 00:24:45.440
Why don't you rest?

00:24:45.720 --> 00:24:47.850
Let me whip up something tasty for you.

00:24:48.710 --> 00:24:51.040
Whose suitcase is this just sitting here?

00:24:52.000 --> 00:24:53.310
Our daughter's!

00:24:53.750 --> 00:24:55.030
Our daughter is back.

00:24:55.960 --> 00:24:56.960
When did she get back?

00:24:56.960 --> 00:24:57.960
She just got back.

00:24:57.960 --> 00:24:58.490
Let's go.

00:24:58.580 --> 00:24:59.790
How come I didn't see her?

00:24:59.790 --> 00:25:00.880
Let her rest for a while.

00:25:00.880 --> 00:25:01.750
Where is she?

00:25:17.700 --> 00:25:18.480
Old man,

00:25:18.480 --> 00:25:20.280
you really are getting muddled.

00:25:50.110 --> 00:25:51.030
Where's my alcohol?

00:25:51.030 --> 00:25:52.890
Sir, alcohol isn't allowed here.

00:25:54.300 --> 00:25:56.030
Sirs are not allowed to
bring alcohol here.

00:25:56.030 --> 00:25:57.110
Are underlings allowed?

00:25:57.110 --> 00:25:58.110
Definitely not.

00:25:58.200 --> 00:25:59.270
Don't try to stop me.

00:25:59.270 --> 00:26:00.200
I'm leaving right now!

00:26:00.200 --> 00:26:01.550
-You can't go out!
-You can't go out!

00:26:01.550 --> 00:26:02.160
Don't stop me!

00:26:02.160 --> 00:26:02.680
Xiaoman!

00:26:02.680 --> 00:26:04.160
-Come here, Xiaoman!
-Help!

00:26:04.160 --> 00:26:05.200
Let me out!

00:26:05.200 --> 00:26:06.310
You can't go out!

00:26:06.510 --> 00:26:07.440
What's wrong? What's wrong?

00:26:07.440 --> 00:26:08.440
He wants to go out.

00:26:08.580 --> 00:26:10.110
Who keeps upsetting my man all day long?

00:26:10.110 --> 00:26:10.720
So annoying!

00:26:10.720 --> 00:26:12.450
Xiaoman, you have to back me up.

00:26:13.270 --> 00:26:15.530
Come on, let's talk in my office. Come on.

00:26:15.840 --> 00:26:17.400
We'll leave it to you then, Xiaoman.

00:26:17.400 --> 00:26:17.920
Sit.

00:26:18.310 --> 00:26:19.310
What's the matter, man?

00:26:19.310 --> 00:26:21.070
Did our hill-blasting project

00:26:21.070 --> 00:26:22.000
get rejected?

00:26:22.000 --> 00:26:23.270
It got approved.

00:26:23.640 --> 00:26:26.570
But I have to go out
and discuss the details with them.

00:26:26.980 --> 00:26:29.800
And don't we need drinks
when we're having a business dinner?

00:26:29.800 --> 00:26:32.460
Right. You've got to
push this project forward.

00:26:32.470 --> 00:26:34.270
I already have the pipes set up

00:26:34.270 --> 00:26:35.160
for the underwater volcano hot spring.

00:26:35.160 --> 00:26:35.750
If the project doesn't go through,

00:26:35.750 --> 00:26:36.640
all that work will be for nothing!

00:26:36.640 --> 00:26:37.880
We can't let that happen!

00:26:37.880 --> 00:26:39.280
Then, X-Xiaoman, you go.

00:26:39.550 --> 00:26:40.440
Go get some alcohol for me.

00:26:40.440 --> 00:26:41.110
Some Coke, too.

00:26:41.110 --> 00:26:42.550
Let's go negotiate the project
with them together.

00:26:42.550 --> 00:26:43.830
You can't go out of here.

00:26:43.830 --> 00:26:45.440
With our status,
going out to eat with them?

00:26:45.440 --> 00:26:46.680
What a joke.

00:26:46.770 --> 00:26:47.890
Call them all over here.

00:26:47.890 --> 00:26:49.640
Our small table full of dishes
is enough for them.

00:26:49.640 --> 00:26:50.240
No.

00:26:50.510 --> 00:26:52.110
What do we have?

00:26:52.550 --> 00:26:54.480
Well, when it comes to drinking...

00:26:56.090 --> 00:26:58.290
I don't usually tell people about this.

00:26:58.530 --> 00:27:02.450
But we've known each other for so long.

00:27:03.240 --> 00:27:04.900
Let me teach you a thing or two.

00:27:05.200 --> 00:27:07.110
When I first came in,
sometimes I wanted a drink too.

00:27:07.110 --> 00:27:08.570
These little cups here...

00:27:10.470 --> 00:27:11.360
are magic cups.

00:27:13.360 --> 00:27:14.640
Whatever you want to drink...

00:27:14.640 --> 00:27:16.170
At that time, I wanted Coke.

00:27:24.110 --> 00:27:24.790
It's Coke.

00:27:26.110 --> 00:27:27.110
Want a beer?

00:27:32.310 --> 00:27:33.750
Really quenches the thirst.

00:27:33.750 --> 00:27:36.470
Sometimes, I want some baijiu with food.

00:27:46.110 --> 00:27:47.060
Xiaoman...

00:27:48.640 --> 00:27:49.830
are you crazy?

00:27:52.670 --> 00:27:53.190
Mom.

00:27:53.480 --> 00:27:55.010
-Sweetie.
-Let me help you.

00:27:55.400 --> 00:27:57.590
No need. Go do your own thing.

00:27:57.590 --> 00:27:59.050
I want to learn to cook too.

00:27:59.750 --> 00:28:02.080
You're a young girl. Why bother learning?

00:28:02.770 --> 00:28:04.970
Look, you'll get oil all over yourself.

00:28:07.430 --> 00:28:08.760
Did your dad just go out?

00:28:09.110 --> 00:28:09.640
Sweetie,

00:28:09.910 --> 00:28:11.200
put the wood ear mushrooms in!

00:28:11.200 --> 00:28:12.660
They must be fully cooked!

00:28:13.210 --> 00:28:14.560
-Yan!
-Mom, I…

00:28:14.920 --> 00:28:15.440
I...

00:28:15.440 --> 00:28:17.070
Yan, what did you go out for?

00:28:17.310 --> 00:28:19.170
I have some business at the plant.

00:28:19.350 --> 00:28:20.440
Don't follow me! No need to follow me!

00:28:20.440 --> 00:28:21.640
It's time for dinner!

00:28:21.830 --> 00:28:22.890
You guys eat first!

00:28:25.000 --> 00:28:26.730
What's wrong? Are you alright?

00:28:27.440 --> 00:28:28.440
What happened...

00:28:28.510 --> 00:28:30.790
See? I told you not to follow me.

00:28:30.790 --> 00:28:31.920
You twisted your ankle, didn't you?

00:28:31.920 --> 00:28:33.640
Let's go. Slow down.

00:28:35.000 --> 00:28:36.240
You're so troublesome.

00:28:36.240 --> 00:28:37.000
Look at you.

00:28:37.850 --> 00:28:38.610
Hurry.

00:28:38.630 --> 00:28:39.680
Mom, are you alright?

00:28:39.680 --> 00:28:40.520
She sprained her ankle!

00:28:40.520 --> 00:28:41.240
What?

00:28:41.240 --> 00:28:42.440
She insisted on following me.

00:28:42.440 --> 00:28:44.070
It's all your dad's fault!

00:28:44.070 --> 00:28:45.550
What happened? What happened?

00:28:45.550 --> 00:28:47.030
Just sit here. Come on.

00:28:47.720 --> 00:28:48.720
She twisted her ankle. Get her that spray.

00:28:48.720 --> 00:28:49.590
I'll go get it. I'll go.

00:28:49.590 --> 00:28:51.000
That Yunnan Baiyao spray.

00:28:51.000 --> 00:28:53.270
It's in the usual place. The usual place.

00:28:53.720 --> 00:28:54.720
Hurry up.

00:28:55.160 --> 00:28:56.290
Be careful.

00:28:57.590 --> 00:28:59.030
You darn old man...

00:28:59.830 --> 00:29:00.750
Dad, let me do it.

00:29:00.750 --> 00:29:01.510
Go and sit on the couch.

00:29:01.510 --> 00:29:02.030
Can you handle it?

00:29:02.030 --> 00:29:02.830
I've got it.

00:29:04.920 --> 00:29:06.240
Your memory isn't great,

00:29:06.240 --> 00:29:07.790
but you run so fast!

00:29:08.400 --> 00:29:10.260
You're faster than young people.

00:29:13.600 --> 00:29:14.770
Mom, I need to take a call.

00:29:14.770 --> 00:29:15.210
Dad.

00:29:15.240 --> 00:29:16.450
I'll do it. Let me.

00:29:23.830 --> 00:29:24.440
Hello?

00:29:27.160 --> 00:29:27.550
I...

00:29:29.400 --> 00:29:30.000
I know.

00:29:30.000 --> 00:29:32.660
I definitely won't let the project
fall behind.

00:29:34.510 --> 00:29:36.000
Something did come up on my end!

00:29:36.000 --> 00:29:37.510
My computer broke.

00:29:39.000 --> 00:29:40.270
But there is a whole team.

00:29:40.270 --> 00:29:41.640
The whole team is working on this project.

00:29:41.640 --> 00:29:42.510
I am the project lead,

00:29:42.510 --> 00:29:43.640
but that doesn't mean

00:29:43.640 --> 00:29:45.030
everything falls on me
whenever something happens.

00:29:45.030 --> 00:29:46.430
There are so many people!

00:29:47.110 --> 00:29:48.000
It doesn't mean I alone

00:29:48.000 --> 00:29:49.640
can finish everything!

00:29:50.440 --> 00:29:50.960
Look.

00:29:51.590 --> 00:29:53.750
-It's all red.
-It'll swell a bit later,

00:29:53.750 --> 00:29:54.950
but it's not serious.

00:29:55.110 --> 00:29:56.350
I know, I know.

00:30:00.030 --> 00:30:01.510
I promise the project won't be delayed.

00:30:01.510 --> 00:30:02.920
As soon as my computer is fixed,

00:30:02.920 --> 00:30:04.480
I'll get right back to work.

00:30:05.170 --> 00:30:06.970
It definitely won't be delayed.

00:30:10.790 --> 00:30:12.030
I promise.

00:30:22.230 --> 00:30:24.090
Ever since we came back this time,

00:30:24.120 --> 00:30:25.600
I don't know what's gotten into your mom.

00:30:25.600 --> 00:30:27.130
She just won't let me go out.

00:30:27.510 --> 00:30:29.370
Isn't it nice to get out for a walk?

00:30:29.720 --> 00:30:31.150
Well, I'm back now.

00:30:31.170 --> 00:30:33.850
I'll walk with you more often from now on.

00:30:34.890 --> 00:30:36.240
That's my daughter.

00:30:36.400 --> 00:30:37.660
My own flesh and blood.

00:30:38.640 --> 00:30:39.510
Xiaodan?

00:30:40.570 --> 00:30:41.050
Lulu?

00:30:41.080 --> 00:30:42.010
Why are you back?

00:30:42.200 --> 00:30:43.590
-I just came back a while ago.
-Chief Engineer Yan.

00:30:43.590 --> 00:30:44.440
This girl...

00:30:45.470 --> 00:30:46.670
What? What do you mean?

00:30:46.670 --> 00:30:48.270
Don't recognize me anymore?

00:30:50.680 --> 00:30:51.550
I remember now.

00:30:52.030 --> 00:30:52.640
You're

00:30:52.640 --> 00:30:54.330
Accountant Wang from
the finance department.

00:30:54.330 --> 00:30:55.070
Accountant Wang?

00:30:55.070 --> 00:30:56.640
She's Sun Lulu, my high school classmate,

00:30:56.640 --> 00:30:57.110
Dad.

00:30:57.130 --> 00:30:57.640
-Yes.
-Your classmate.

00:30:57.640 --> 00:30:59.270
She's with
the plant's finance department now.

00:30:59.270 --> 00:30:59.750
I'm Sun Lulu.

00:30:59.750 --> 00:31:00.380
You're classmates.

00:31:00.380 --> 00:31:01.890
Alright. It's nice for you two
to catch up.

00:31:01.890 --> 00:31:03.000
You two chat for a bit. Chat.

00:31:03.000 --> 00:31:04.270
It's not often
you two get to see each other.

00:31:04.270 --> 00:31:04.790
Okay, okay.

00:31:04.790 --> 00:31:05.200
Bye, Chief Engineer Yan.

00:31:05.200 --> 00:31:06.460
I'll go sit over there.

00:31:09.270 --> 00:31:10.480
You look so great!

00:31:11.160 --> 00:31:11.720
I'm telling you,

00:31:11.720 --> 00:31:13.400
our plant is bustling now.

00:31:13.400 --> 00:31:15.880
You big earners from abroad are all back.

00:31:17.480 --> 00:31:18.000
It's great.

00:31:18.000 --> 00:31:19.590
All... all back?

00:31:19.880 --> 00:31:20.880
They're all back.

00:31:21.240 --> 00:31:22.550
What do you mean? Xiao...

00:31:22.550 --> 00:31:23.720
Xiaoman is back too?

00:31:24.380 --> 00:31:26.310
He came back from Japan a while ago.

00:31:27.070 --> 00:31:29.000
What? You haven't seen him?

00:31:33.900 --> 00:31:35.770
It's normal if you haven't.

00:31:38.070 --> 00:31:39.200
What? Why?

00:31:39.880 --> 00:31:41.280
He's in the hospital now.

00:31:41.890 --> 00:31:42.750
He... He...

00:31:43.000 --> 00:31:44.010
He's hospitalized?

00:31:44.010 --> 00:31:44.680
W-why?

00:31:44.680 --> 00:31:46.200
Was he injured or sick?

00:31:46.200 --> 00:31:48.240
No, I heard

00:31:48.240 --> 00:31:50.000
he had some sort of mental breakdown.

00:31:50.000 --> 00:31:51.160
-Mental breakdown?
-I don't know what happened.

00:31:51.160 --> 00:31:54.090
He's been that way
ever since he came back from Japan.

00:31:54.880 --> 00:31:55.610
You're back!

00:31:58.730 --> 00:32:00.040
Guess who I ran into today.

00:32:00.040 --> 00:32:01.430
Who could you possibly have run into?

00:32:01.430 --> 00:32:01.950
Guess.

00:32:02.640 --> 00:32:03.350
Fatty Liu.

00:32:04.310 --> 00:32:06.040
Did you just run into Fatty Liu?

00:32:06.270 --> 00:32:07.200
I'm telling you,

00:32:07.270 --> 00:32:09.310
you chose me over him.

00:32:09.310 --> 00:32:10.990
Don't you go pulling any funny business.

00:32:10.990 --> 00:32:11.920
No, Wang Dongdong,

00:32:11.920 --> 00:32:13.590
are you out of your mind?

00:32:14.160 --> 00:32:15.420
Fatty Liu? Seriously?

00:32:15.470 --> 00:32:16.920
I ran into Xiaodan!

00:32:17.480 --> 00:32:18.810
She's back from France.

00:32:18.840 --> 00:32:19.400
Xiaodan?

00:32:22.940 --> 00:32:24.830
She was doing well there.
Why did she come back?

00:32:24.830 --> 00:32:26.000
How would I know?

00:32:26.880 --> 00:32:29.880
Anyway, I told her about
Xiaoman being hospitalized.

00:32:30.000 --> 00:32:31.800
Why did you have to tell her that?

00:32:32.150 --> 00:32:33.790
Why couldn't I tell her?

00:32:33.790 --> 00:32:35.680
Are they never going to
see each other again?

00:32:35.680 --> 00:32:38.270
I mean, what are they even supposed to say
if they meet?

00:32:38.270 --> 00:32:40.310
Look how down and out Xiaoman is now.

00:32:40.310 --> 00:32:41.920
He definitely wouldn't want Xiaodan
to know!

00:32:41.920 --> 00:32:43.360
Tell me, what man...

00:32:44.070 --> 00:32:44.920
would want his ex-girlfriend to see him

00:32:44.920 --> 00:32:46.580
when he's at his lowest point?

00:32:46.750 --> 00:32:48.200
What do you mean by that?

00:32:48.880 --> 00:32:49.880
Besides,

00:32:49.920 --> 00:32:50.830
can you really say that Xiaoman ending up

00:32:50.830 --> 00:32:52.550
like this has nothing to do with Xiaodan?

00:32:52.550 --> 00:32:54.480
She has to know, one way or another.

00:32:55.000 --> 00:32:56.270
Maybe she'll soften up,

00:32:56.270 --> 00:32:57.550
and they can get back together.

00:32:57.550 --> 00:32:58.350
Give me a break.

00:32:58.350 --> 00:32:59.830
It's been so long.

00:32:59.920 --> 00:33:01.720
They've probably both moved on.

00:33:02.210 --> 00:33:04.340
How could they move on that fast?

00:33:05.670 --> 00:33:07.870
You want to visit Zhang Xiaoman, right?

00:33:08.880 --> 00:33:10.310
You're his friend?

00:33:11.350 --> 00:33:12.240
Yes.

00:33:13.100 --> 00:33:15.920
It's just that we haven't been in touch
or seen each other for a long time.

00:33:15.920 --> 00:33:18.050
So I only know he's hospitalized here.

00:33:18.990 --> 00:33:21.120
We call him Xiaoman, the Chime Ringer.

00:33:21.480 --> 00:33:23.070
He's much happier than any of us.

00:33:23.070 --> 00:33:23.680
When he's free,

00:33:23.680 --> 00:33:25.030
he helps us nurses with carrying medicine,

00:33:25.030 --> 00:33:26.200
ringing the wind chime,
and things like that.

00:33:26.200 --> 00:33:29.300
Once he takes off his hospital gown,
he can walk out just like a normal person.

00:33:29.300 --> 00:33:29.760
Come on.

00:33:31.230 --> 00:33:32.090
Please come in.

00:33:51.260 --> 00:33:52.860
The world is what's eternal.

00:33:53.350 --> 00:33:55.680
After long periods of
gathering and condensing,

00:33:55.680 --> 00:33:58.340
every individual becomes
an individual again.

00:34:00.170 --> 00:34:02.440
Thus, energy forms
a permanently closed loop.

00:34:02.440 --> 00:34:04.240
Xiaoman is probably in his room.

00:34:04.350 --> 00:34:05.550
I'll go check for you.

00:34:06.000 --> 00:34:06.720
Three laps.

00:34:07.310 --> 00:34:09.110
After long periods of evolution

00:34:09.360 --> 00:34:10.560
and transformation,

00:34:10.710 --> 00:34:12.239
moving towards the future.

00:34:19.030 --> 00:34:19.690
Xiaoman...

00:34:25.210 --> 00:34:26.320
Well, Miss,

00:34:26.320 --> 00:34:27.230
Xiaoman isn't in his room.

00:34:27.230 --> 00:34:29.090
He's probably at the greenhouse.

00:34:30.510 --> 00:34:32.320
Where is the greenhouse?

00:34:32.710 --> 00:34:33.670
Go down to the first floor,

00:34:33.670 --> 00:34:34.530
then turn left.

00:34:34.880 --> 00:34:36.030
There are people doing aerobics there.

00:34:36.030 --> 00:34:37.280
You'll find the greenhouse right there.

00:34:37.280 --> 00:34:37.960
It's fine. Wait for me.

00:34:37.960 --> 00:34:39.090
I'll take you there.

00:34:39.310 --> 00:34:39.949
Let's go.

00:35:34.670 --> 00:35:37.270
Zhang Xiaoman, does this purple one
look nice?

00:35:37.510 --> 00:35:38.310
Yeah, it does.

00:35:40.320 --> 00:35:43.480
You know, hanging these empty bottles here

00:35:43.510 --> 00:35:44.760
and letting them sway—

00:35:44.760 --> 00:35:46.020
they look really nice.

00:35:46.560 --> 00:35:47.920
You're really creative.

00:35:47.920 --> 00:35:49.380
Let me tell you something.

00:35:49.680 --> 00:35:51.250
You kids
from industrial and mining families

00:35:51.250 --> 00:35:52.510
probably wouldn't understand.

00:35:52.510 --> 00:35:53.550
When I was little,

00:35:53.670 --> 00:35:56.070
all my clothes were hand-me-downs—
old things

00:35:56.070 --> 00:35:57.340
other families didn't want anymore.

00:35:57.340 --> 00:35:59.420
I remember I had a cousin

00:35:59.760 --> 00:36:01.840
who had a really beautiful doll.

00:36:02.190 --> 00:36:03.440
But it got old and dirty,

00:36:03.440 --> 00:36:05.300
so she didn't want it anymore
and gave it to me.

00:36:05.300 --> 00:36:07.920
I gathered all the scrap fabric
I could find around the house

00:36:07.920 --> 00:36:09.520
and sewed new clothes for it.

00:36:09.760 --> 00:36:12.000
I even crushed some garden balsam petals

00:36:12.000 --> 00:36:13.440
to dye its hair red.

00:36:13.800 --> 00:36:14.800
At that moment, I felt

00:36:14.800 --> 00:36:15.760
that my doll

